# Week 5 — Baseline Network Traffic Analysis

## Overview

Week 5 focuses on analyzing **normal network behavior within the ICS environment**.
Understanding baseline communication patterns is essential for detecting abnormal activities during simulated cyber incidents.

During this phase, network traffic between the SCADA system and PLC was captured and analyzed to identify **standard communication patterns and protocol usage**.

Packet analysis was performed using **Wireshark**, which allows detailed inspection of industrial network traffic.

The collected baseline data will later be used to compare against abnormal traffic generated during attack simulations.

---

# Objectives

The main objectives of this phase include:

* Capture normal ICS network traffic
* Analyze Modbus communication patterns
* Identify typical network behavior
* Document baseline traffic characteristics
* Prepare reference data for anomaly detection

---

# Network Communication Overview

In the ICS-RedSim environment, communication occurs between the SCADA system and the PLC using the **Modbus TCP protocol**.

### Communication Flow

```
SCADA System (FUXA)
        |
        | Modbus TCP
        |
PLC Controller (OpenPLC)
        |
        |
Industrial Process Simulation
```

This communication allows the SCADA system to read process variables and send control commands to the PLC.

---

# Network Monitoring Tool

Network traffic analysis was performed using **Wireshark**.

### Key Features Used

* Packet capture
* Protocol analysis
* Traffic filtering
* Network statistics

Wireshark enables detailed analysis of industrial protocols such as Modbus.

---

# Baseline Traffic Capture

During normal system operation, packet captures were recorded while the SCADA dashboard monitored and controlled the simulated tank process.

The captured traffic primarily consisted of:

* Periodic register reads
* Coil write operations
* Request-response communication between SCADA and PLC

These packets represent the standard behavior of an industrial control system.

---

# Modbus Protocol Analysis

The industrial communication protocol used in the lab is **Modbus TCP**, one of the most widely used protocols in industrial automation.

### Common Modbus Functions Observed

| Function Code | Operation              |
| ------------- | ---------------------- |
| 01            | Read Coils             |
| 03            | Read Holding Registers |
| 05            | Write Single Coil      |
| 06            | Write Single Register  |

These operations allow the SCADA system to monitor sensor data and control actuators.

---

# Normal Traffic Characteristics

The baseline traffic exhibited the following characteristics:

| Feature               | Observation      |
| --------------------- | ---------------- |
| Protocol              | Modbus TCP       |
| Port                  | TCP 502          |
| Communication Pattern | Request-response |
| Traffic Volume        | Low              |
| Polling Interval      | Periodic         |

These patterns represent normal industrial communication behavior.

